The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Sharp rise in Visa Steel profit
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Sharp rise in Visa Steel profit
          OUR BUREAU                      Visa Steel chairman Vishambhar Saran in Calcutta on Wednesday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury                           
	Calcutta, May 19: Visa Steel  a part of the Rs 5,000-crore Visa group  has posted a 170.98 per cent rise in profit after tax at Rs 47.42 crore in 2009-10 against a loss of Rs 66.81 crore a year ago.        
	Profit before tax grew 185.79 per cent to Rs 85.68 crore during the reporting fiscal. Revenues rose 12.59 per cent to Rs 1,171.48 crore, while earnings before interest, depreciation, taxes and amortisation increased 635.15 per cent to Rs 197.63 crore. The company plans to set up an integrated steel plant at Kalinganagar industrial complex in Orissa.         
	HNG show        
	Hindusthan National Glass amp; Industries (HNG) has posted a 45 per cent rise in net profit in 2009-10 at Rs 155 crore compared with Rs 107 crore last year. Net sales grew to Rs 1,360 crore from Rs 1,311 crore a year ago. EPS grew 44 per cent to Rs 17.77 from Rs 12.34 a year ago.         
	Berger Paints        
	Berger Paints Indias profit after tax for the quarter ended March 2010 has jumped 31 per cent to Rs 28.17 crore from Rs 21.49 crore a year ago. Net sales grew 24 per cent to Rs 434.5 crore from Rs 350.7 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                      
